    "text": "I add a feature and add a toggle of state for it. Then I add another feature and add another toggle. Do I really need to handle 4 possible states now, or just 3, i.e. I have an enum in disguise :disguised_face:? I keep making this mistake. Designing things up front is easy, but I find it impossible to reliably avoid mistakes when adding to an existing design.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "aVaoM",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I add a feature and add a toggle of state for it. Then I add another feature and add another toggle. Do I really need to handle 4 possible states now, or just 3, i.e. I have an enum in disguise "
              },
              {
                "type": "emoji",
                "name": "disguised_face",
                "unicode": "1f978"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "? I keep making this mistake. Designing things up front is easy, but I find it impossible to reliably avoid mistakes when adding to an existing design."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
